_header: O Cupid I grant thy might is much

HunHM28175.First Lines:
O Cupid I graunt thy might is muchfor sure thov loveth they dart
                        to shout at such…
HunHM28175.Note:
Added to blank page after a collection of prayers to Christ, written as
                    prose, by the sixteenth-century hand of George Conyers.
